definitions.definition: A cone -shaped tent traditionally used by many native peoples of the Great Plains of North America.
A conical formation of small flammable sticks leaning on each other, in roughly the shape of an Indian teepee, built over smaller tinder such as cotton or leaves.

main_definition: A cone -shaped tent traditionally used by many native peoples of the Great Plains of North America.
